        <div class="faq-group">
            <h2 class="faq-group-title">Is this for you?</h2>
            <details><summary>Is this like antivirus or a VPN?</summary><p>No. Those are generic, always-on tools. This is a one-time, in-person hardening of your specific devices, accounts, and exposure — calibrated to your situation.</p></details>
            <details><summary>How is this different from IT support?</summary><p>IT support fixes problems after they happen. We harden, model the threat, and train you — closing the vulnerabilities before anyone uses them, on the same endpoint standards applied to government systems.</p></details>
            <details><summary>Do you work with individuals or companies?</summary><p>Individuals, and the people around them. The service exists for people in high-pressure personal situations — separation, dispute, inheritance, competitive exposure — not corporate IT procurement.</p></details>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-group">
            <h2 class="faq-group-title">Confidentiality</h2>
            <details><summary>Will anyone know I contacted you?</summary><p>No. Nothing is shared. WhatsApp and Signal are end-to-end encrypted; nothing passes through a form or a third party.</p></details>
            <details><summary>Do you keep records of what you found on my device?</summary><p>No. What we find during the day is handled during the day. Nothing is logged, copied, or stored.</p></details>
            <details><summary>Is there a file on me after the engagement?</summary><p>No. The only document that leaves is the Certificate of Hardening — and it stays with you. We keep no copy.</p></details>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-group">
            <h2 class="faq-group-title">What actually happens</h2>
            <details><summary>Can this be done online or remotely?</summary><p>No. Remote access is a door into your device; handing it to a security provider is no safer than handing it to anyone else. Everything is done in person, in your presence.</p></details>
            <details><summary>Where do you operate? Will you come to me?</summary><p>We come to you. Primarily Israel; international engagements by arrangement.</p></details>
            <details><summary>How long does an engagement take?</summary><p>Personal Shield is one day. Home Shield, two to four. Inner Circle Shield depends on the number of people covered. The schedule is agreed before we begin.</p></details>
            <details><summary>What do I need to bring or prepare?</summary><p>Your devices and your account credentials, which you enter yourself — we never handle passwords. Bring your account details, your account of what's happened, and anything suspicious you've noticed. Everything else is handled on site.</p></details>
            <details><summary>What is the Certificate of Hardening?</summary><p>A signed record issued at the end of the day: the steps applied, the standards used, and the date. Yours to keep; no copy retained.</p></details>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-group">
            <h2 class="faq-group-title">Who does this</h2>
            <details><summary>Who does the work?</summary><p>Dr. Lior Tabansky — directly. Not a team, not a junior technician supervised remotely. The person who assesses your threat is the person who hardens your devices and accounts.</p></details>
            <details><summary>Can I verify Dr. Tabansky's background independently?</summary><p>Yes. The full record — publications, academic positions, government advisory roles, media — is public, at <a href="https://cyberdrtabansky.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cyberdrtabansky.com</a>, so you can verify without taking our word for it. <a href="/en/why-us.html">More about the method &rarr;</a></p></details>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-group">
            <h2 class="faq-group-title">Pricing and tiers</h2>
            <details><summary>How much does it cost?</summary><p>Four protection tiers: Personal Shield ₪14,000, Home Shield ₪33,000, Inner Circle Shield ₪38,000, Sovereign Shield ₪95,000. A Threat Assessment is ₪3,500, credited in full toward any tier within 14 days. <a href="/en/pricing.html">See the four protection tiers &rarr;</a></p></details>
            <details><summary>What's the difference between the tiers?</summary><p>Scope, not quality. Personal Shield covers one person's primary device and accounts; Home adds the home network and up to two more devices (a vehicle and further devices are add-ons); Inner Circle adds people, typically three, each fully hardened; Sovereign is comprehensive, adding physical counter-surveillance and ongoing monitoring. The hardening standard is identical across all four.</p></details>
            <details><summary>What is the Threat Assessment, and do I need it?</summary><p>A three-hour, in-person review of your current exposure that produces a threat map and a recommended scope. It isn't required — some clients arrive knowing what they need — but if you're unsure which tier fits, it's the right first step, and its ₪3,500 comes off the tier you choose within 14 days.</p></details>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-group">
            <h2 class="faq-group-title">After the engagement</h2>
            <details><summary>Is the protection permanent?</summary><p>The hardening is durable — devices stay hardened, accounts stay secured, hardware keys don't expire. What changes over time is the threat landscape: new vulnerabilities, credential leaks, evolving methods. That's what Annual Watch addresses.</p></details>
            <details><summary>What are Annual Watch and the Priority Retainer?</summary><p>Two optional products for past clients. Annual Watch (₪7,000 a year): credential-leak scanning, breach alerts, and one in-person account-hygiene check each year. Priority Retainer (₪14,000 a year): response inside eight business hours and three in-person check-ins a year. Both are included in Sovereign Shield, and neither needs remote access.</p></details>
        </div>
    </div>
